      },
      "date": "2011-06-07 17:31:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Looks good to me, approved\n\nI know that there are a lot more such messages in the Lustre source that should be changed as well.\n\nRather than hard-code them in the source, however, I think it best to create something like one or both of:\n\n#define LUSTRE_BUGREPORT_URL \"http://bugs.whamcloud.com/\n#define LUSTRE_SUPPORT_URL   \"http://wiki.whamcloud.com/\n\nand then use those in the source so that they can be updated more easily.  For example lustre/lvfs/fsfilt_ext3.c, lustre/obdclass/class_obd.c, lustre/obdfilter/filter.c, lustre/obdfilter/filter_io_26.c, lustre/osc/osc_request.c, and lustre/utils/mkfs_lustre.c all have \"contact\" URLs.\n\nThere are also a few \"quaint\" error messages still left in the code that could be replaced at the same time:\n\nllu_inode_revalidate()\n                CERROR(\"REPORT THIS LINE TO PETER\\n\");\n\n__ll_inode_revalidate_it()\n                CERROR(\"REPORT THIS LINE TO PETER\\n\");\nll_lookup_it()\n                CERROR(\"Tell Peter, lookup on mtpt, it %s\\n\", LL_IT2STR(it));\nll_unhash_aliases()\n                CERROR(\"unexpected NULL inode, tell phil\\n\");\n\n\nNote also that the URL for the GPLv2.pdf file in the header does not work anymore, so we might consider replacing it with a URL that does work, but that should be done in a separate patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
